PART: Budget Tracker
NAME: Budget Tracker
STATUS: draft

DATA: Budget Categories
MARKER: budget_categories
INTENT: holds all budget categories and their balances
TAGS: #list
---
The app holds a list of budget categories. Each category has a name, a current balance, and a monthly limit.

STRUCTURE: Budget Screen
MARKER: budget_screen
INTENT: the main screen showing all budget categories and their balances
---
The screen has a header with the app name, a section for each budget category with its name, current balance, and monthly limit, and a floating add category button in the bottom right.

WHEN: Add Category
MARKER: add_category
INTENT: user adds a new budget category
TAGS: #form, #list, #user
---
When the user taps the add category button, a form appears. The user fills in the category name and monthly limit. The new category is added to the list and displayed on the budget screen.

WHEN: Update Category
MARKER: update_category
INTENT: user updates an existing budget category
TAGS: #form, #list, #user
---
When the user taps the edit icon on a category, a form appears. The user can modify the category name and monthly limit. After confirming, the changes are reflected in the list and on the budget screen.

ASSERT: Category Balance
MARKER: category_balance
INTENT: ensure category balance does not exceed limit
TAGS: #user
---
A category's current balance cannot exceed its monthly limit. If the balance would exceed the limit, the user is prompted to adjust the balance or the limit.

SURFACE: Category Name
MARKER: category_name
INTENT: label for category name input
TAGS: #form, #input
---
The add category form and edit category form have a label "Category Name" for the input field.

SURFACE: Monthly Limit
MARKER: monthly_limit
INTENT: label for monthly limit input
TAGS: #form, #input
---
The add category form and edit category form have a label "Monthly Limit" for the input field.